## Tools

- **anki-ai**: headless Anki CLI at `~/.local/bin/anki-ai`.
  Run `anki-ai skill` to load full usage docs once before any Anki operation.
  Auth stored at `~/.config/anki-ai/auth.json` (already configured).
  Collection auto-detected from `~/.local/share/Anki2/`.

- **Obsidian vault**: `{{ obsidian_vault }}`
  Write notes as `.md` files directly into this directory tree.
  Vault contains AGENTS.md with more information.

## Anki Workflow Rules

- Sync before reading if freshness matters; sync after every write session.
- Snapshot (`anki-ai snapshot`) before any bulk add/update/delete session.
- Use `--yes` on all destructive commands (delete, restore).
- Never run interactive commands — use `--email`/`--password` flags or env vars
  for auth.
